'wohl'), fits all the passages (in the Brâhma*n*as at all events) where
*s*a*s*vat occurs.

<span id="fn_195"></span>[98:3](sbe4120.htm#fr_195.md) See above, [V, 1, 4,
3](sbe4106.htm#5:1:4:3.md) seq.

<span id="fn_196"></span>[99:1](sbe4120.htm#fr_196.md) Pra*s*âst*ri*, 'the
director,' is also another name for the Maitrâvaru*n*a priest.

<span id="fn_197"></span>[99:2](sbe4120.htm#fr_197.md) That is, the cows
given to priests as sacrificial fee. For particulars regarding the
passage by which they are driven to their destination, see part ii, p.
344, note 1.

<span id="fn_198"></span>[99:3](sbe4120.htm#fr_198.md) Probably here 'for
well-being;' the author, however, evidently takes it here in the sense
