<span id="fn_203"></span>[102:1](sbe4120.htm#fr_203.md) ? Or, means vigour,
Indra.

<span id="fn_204"></span>[103:1](sbe4120.htm#fr_204.md) Or perhaps, 'in the
best place (vara).' See [VI, 7, 3, 11](sbe4151.htm#6:7:3:11.md).

<span id="fn_205"></span>[104:1](sbe4120.htm#fr_205.md) According to Taitt.
Br. I, 7, 9, 6, the king, on returning to the Vedi, is supposed to have
ascended to the heavenly world (suvargaloka), from which the charioteer
is to be excluded by this expedient.

<span id="fn_206"></span>[104:2](sbe4120.htm#fr_206.md) The Âhavanîya of
the hall (the so-called 'hall-door fire') has been lifted and placed on
a cart.

<span id="fn_207"></span>[104:3](sbe4120.htm#fr_207.md) Or, two round
